From d3913acf6947dc06dba64aa242e3046900516e11 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 23:34:35 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 22/39] inline-3d(#625): WIP scroll-sync Phase 1 (per-element
 concurrent submit) + Phase 2 (impl-side scroll-fresh rects)

Phase 1: DisplayXRWeaveGpu keeps a per-target keyed-mutex input pool (flat_map
keyed by target_id) with per-element in-flight; WeaveCompositedSurface submits
every visible element each frame (drops the round-robin) and draws each woven at
its submit-time rect. Kills the ~N-frame round-robin lag + wrong-region smear.

Phase 2: LayerTreeHostImpl::MakeCompositorFrameMetadata shifts inline_3d_rects by
the viewport's impl-accumulated scroll delta (SyncedScrollOffset::Delta() x dsf),
so the weave rect tracks the pixels presented THIS frame (kills rect-report lag).

Residual is the inherent ~1-frame ASYNC round-trip floor (GPU-process weave RPC
must be async). Next: GPU-process SYNCHRONOUS weave to remove it (see memory).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
